function [C]=holecosC(D,param);% holecosC                  - cosinusoidal hole effect covariance model (Jan 1,2001)%% Compute the cosinusoidal hole effect covariance matrix% from a distance matrix.%% SYNTAX :%% [C]=holecosC(D,param);%% INPUT :%% D       n by m   distance matrix, having real values >=0.% param   1 by 2   vector of parameters such that param(1) is the%                  half amplitude and param(2) is half the periodicity%                  of the hole effect.%% OUTPUT :%% C       n by m   covariance matrix with same size as D.%% NOTE :%% This model is only valid in a 1-dimensional space.C=param(1)*cos(pi*D/param(2));